# Architecture conventions

## Module structure
- All domain logic lives in `src/modules/<name>/`.
- Each module has the following layout:
  - `index.ts` — the **only** import surface for code outside the module
  - `actions/` — server actions (`"use server"`), input-validated with Zod
  - `services/` — pure server functions over Prisma (testable, reusable)
  - `queries.ts` — read-side helpers, wrapped in `unstable_cache` with tags
  - `schemas/` — Zod schemas (single source of truth)
  - `components/` — React components scoped to this domain
  - `types.ts` — DTOs and re-exports

## Boundary rules (enforced by ESLint)
- Files outside `src/modules/X` **must** import only from `@/modules/X` (not `@/modules/X/services/...`).
- This keeps refactors local — the module's internal layout can change without breaking consumers.

## Server-only enforcement
- Every file under `services/`, `queries.ts`, `actions/`, and `src/lib/db.ts`, `razorpay.ts`, `cloudinary.ts`, `resend.ts` starts with `import "server-only"`.
- Server SDK clients (Razorpay, Cloudinary, Resend, Prisma) are **lazy-instantiated** inside a `get<Client>()` helper, never at module top-level — otherwise `next build`'s static collect-page-data pass will throw when env vars are absent.
- This prevents secrets and Prisma client from leaking into client bundles.

## Data access
- **Only** `services/` and `queries.ts` may import `@/lib/db`. Actions and route handlers go through services.
- All Prisma queries that read from FTS or use raw SQL live in `services/` files clearly named (e.g. `services/search.ts`).

## Path aliases
- `@/*` → `src/*`
- `@/modules/*` → `src/modules/*`
- `@/lib/*` → `src/lib/*`
- `@/components/*` → `src/components/*`
- `@/emails/*` → `emails/*`
